    <item>
      <title>Re: Class Issues List - Update</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=shadowknightbalance&amp;message.id=5509#M5509</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN 10pt; **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE: FONT-FAMILY: Verdana?&gt;&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;1.&amp;nbsp; Knight tanking is closer to Beastlords/Rangers/Monks than it is to Warriors.&amp;nbsp; Being a tank class we should be closer to Warriors than to non tanking dps classes. &lt;SPAN red? **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;(currently being evaluated) - Most likely this will be considered as part of the class re-envisioning&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR: #cccccc?&gt;&lt;xml:namespace prefix = o ns = "urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office" &gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;2.&amp;nbsp; With the amount mobs cast these days SK's have great difficulty fulfiling their secondary role of pulling.&amp;nbsp; If we could have a chance to not have our feigns broken by spells it would help alot. &lt;SPAN red? **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;(currently being discussed) - Most likely this will be considered as part of the class re-envisioning&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR: #cccccc?&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;3.&amp;nbsp; SK's need some line of spells which scales to the mob.&amp;nbsp; Paladins have stuns which always reduce x% of the mobs attack time, Warriors have Defensive/Evasive/Stonewall to always reduce x% of the mobs dps, SK's need a tanking ability that scales.&amp;nbsp; &lt;SPAN red? **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;(currently being evaluated) - Most likely this will be considered as part of the class re-envisioning&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR: #cccccc?&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;4.&amp;nbsp; SK's and Paladins are the only melee classes without a form of Parry/Riposte/Dodge disc.&amp;nbsp; We need one for emergencies and tank switches badly. &lt;SPAN red? **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;(currently being evaluated) - Most likely this will be considered as part of the class re-envisioning&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR: #cccccc?&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;5.&amp;nbsp; Rangers recieved offensive/weapon skill caps equal to Warriors as they're an offensive class.&amp;nbsp; Following the same logic knights should recieve ALL defensive skill caps equal to Warriors rather than just the Defense cap equaling Warriors. &lt;SPAN red? **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;(currently being evaluated) - Most likely this will be considered as part of the class re-envisioning&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR: #cccccc?&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;6.&amp;nbsp; To give SK's more group friendliness we would like a necro like res that uses essence emeralds.&amp;nbsp; One of the main strengths of Knights is that they're supposed to offer utility if our utility benefits ourselves only it doesn't sufficently counter the tanking differences between us and Warriors. &lt;SPAN red? **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;(currently being evaluated) - Most likely this will be considered as part of the class re-envisioning&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR: #cccccc?&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;7.&amp;nbsp; Due to most boss mobs being tuned for defensive in raids it puts too large a strain on a guilds requirement of Warriors.&amp;nbsp; Awhile ago Druids were given better heals allowing them to fill in some for Clerics lessening a guilds dependance on that class.&amp;nbsp; The same thing should be done with Knights giving us a defensive-like disc lessening the necessity for a guild to field 6+ Warriors per raid for the bosses. &lt;SPAN red? **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;(currently being evaluated) - Most likely this will be considered as part of the class re-envisioning&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR: #cccccc?&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;8.&amp;nbsp; Mobs swing faster as they get higher level, with GoD we had lots of trouble channeling spells and in Omens mobs continue to hit faster but we recieve no increase to channeling.&amp;nbsp; All hybrids flat out need higher channeling to perform their jobs better.&amp;nbsp; It also makes sense from a game standpoint since it's our job to cast while being hit. &lt;SPAN red? **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;(currently being evaluated) - Most likely this will be considered as part of the class re-envisioning&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR: #cccccc?&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;9.&amp;nbsp; Aura of Hate is a beneficial spell which is only useful to some clases but cannot be clicked off.&amp;nbsp; This makes the spell line unattractive for many players because the casters/priests in their groups get upset about being buffed with things which are useless to them and cannot be removed.&amp;nbsp; It would help greatly if&amp;nbsp;this could be clicked off.&amp;nbsp; Also, Aura of Pain should be able to be clicked off as well despite being self only. &lt;SPAN red? **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;(currently being evaluated)&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR: #cccccc?&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;10. Our Epic 1.5 and 2 need some changes still even after the recent adjustments. &lt;FONT color=#0033ff&gt;&lt;SPAN red? **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;(currently being evaluated)&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;BR&gt;* The effect was changed from group to single. In it's old form the click was among the weakest effects, there wasn't a reason to change it from group to self only when fixing it's problems. In it's self only form now it is still among the weakest. It's also the only tank class effect which is self only when the fact is that even the current effect as group would only leave it as average compared to the click effects other classes get.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;* If the effect has to remain as self only the recast should be reduced substantially.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;*Two-Handed epics should work with the Shield Block AA and provide the AC over softcap benefit which shields provide. Back in Kunark epics were given the same benefits that using shields at the time possessed (bash enabled). Since then there have been more advantages to using shields put into the game such as AC which raises softcaps and Shield Block. These advantages are huge tradeoffs for tank classes to make when choosing to weild their epic. It would make more sense to see a Pal/Shd using their epic while tanking if these benefits were present on the weapons. &lt;/P&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
